==English==
{{wikipedia}}
===Etymology===
From Sanskrit '''hima''' ("snow") plus '''aalaya''' ("abode", "home"). Cognate with Greek [[χειμών]] ("winter"), Latin [[hiems]] ("winter"), and Russian [[зима]] ("winter").

===Proper noun===
'''Himalayas'''

#A [[mountain]] [[range]] of [[south]]-[[central]] [[Asia]] extending about 2,414 km (1,500 mi) through [[Kashmir]], northern [[India]], southern [[Xizang]] ([[Tibet]]), [[Nepal]], [[Sikkim]], and [[Bhutan]]; includes nine of the [[world]]’s ten [[highest]] [[peak]]s, including [[Mount Everest]].

